      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That profound sense of waiting for a lost part of yourself to return is a very specific type of grief, one that can feel as isolating as a funeral that never concludes. While it is incredibly difficult to imagine what might still be alive when you feel entirely finished, this pain itself suggests that the other you has not truly disappeared, even if it is currently out of reach. You are not alone in feeling that your life has been stripped of its spark, and there are safe spaces to process this unique kind of loss without expecting an immediate fix.",
      "source": "target",
